review_blob: Light with subtle hops. Flavoursome but pale. Fizzy but drinkable. Recommend drinking chilled.

The new golden sister developed the same time as the dark arrowaine. This is my favourite of the two. 
Light and fizzy but sweet and citrus taste. My preference is chilled.

Wychwood (anti) Christmas beer. 
Citrus and cinnamon undertones. Damson and sweet notes. Interesting difference between room temperature and chilled. Very nice.

Very dark and flavoursome. 
Smells like a stout but mild. Little coffee undertones and subtle flavours.
Dark new beer. Very light and watery despite the darkness and appearance. Has the aroma of a darker thicker ale. Bit disappointing.

Very nice golden sister of hobgoblin. 
Sweet and citric and very drinkable. Light and with a bit of fizz. 
My preference is chilled and from a straight glass. Gives a slight thick white head.

The best of a brilliant bunch. 
Lovely beer bottled or cask. 
Nice fizz and light head, lovely ruby colouring, and very drinkable. No real difference between cask (4.8%) and bottled (5.2%).
Light summery drink, brief thin head. Initial fizz holds with a few bubbles. Hoppy light flavour very drinkable.
Strong deep white head, held well because the beer is highly carbonated, dark straw like golden colour. taste is a little watery, hints of spice and malt. Drinkable.
beer_name: Shepherd Neame Whitstable Bay Pale Ale (Bottle)

review_blob: Brilliant white head, straw like colour, very carbonated. Bitter smell and taste, hint of citrus. It's very nice, nothing more though. Doesn't taste like a 5.6%. Drinkable.
Bottle at home. Nice deep Amber colouring with off white head. Flavour falls a little flat for me, bland and lacking depth. Too carbonated with constant small bubbles detracting from the taste.
Bottle (500ml) at home. Pale Amber appearance, brief white head. Nice aroma of citrus and hops. Taste is ok, but very carbonated and gets in the way of what could have been a very nice beer.
Nice. Hoppy in taste and aroma, and lovely appearance. Low percentage and very drinkable.
Lovely colour and aroma. Very refreshing. A very highly rated bronze. I have had this both cask at the brewery (superb) and bottled (just as good, if a little fizzy!)
